    "On the one hand, the research questions themselves were exploratory, and the researcher expected participants to provide more cognitive information.",
    "On the other hand, this phenomenon may also reflect the divergent and creative thinking of art learning, requiring questions that encourage participants to reflect freely after satisfying the research objectives.",
    "RQ6: Potential improvements.",
    "In addition to exploring how effectively employ SR in education, the current review also points to possible future directions on SR research with existing models of computer-supported learning and technology-assisted instruction.",
    "Enhancing the dependability of outcomes through the synthesis of multifaceted data sources."
